columns.name: id
columns.description: A unique identifier automatically assigned to each part of a multipart file upload in the S3-compatible storage system. This serves as the primary key to distinguish individual chunks or segments that make up a larger file being uploaded in pieces.

columns.name: upload_id
columns.description: Unique identifier that associates individual parts with their parent multipart upload operation in S3 storage. Links uploaded file chunks to enable proper reassembly into the complete file.

columns.name: size
columns.description: The byte size of an individual part within a multipart upload to S3 storage. Defaults to zero when no data has been uploaded for the part.

columns.name: part_number
columns.description: The sequential identifier for individual parts within a multipart upload operation, used to maintain the correct order when reassembling the complete file. This value determines the position of each chunk in the final assembled object.

columns.name: bucket_id
columns.description: Identifies the specific S3 storage bucket that contains the multipart upload parts. This serves as a reference to link upload parts with their designated storage container.

columns.name: key
columns.description: Purpose unclear from available data. Without sample values, the specific meaning of this required text field in the S3 multipart uploads parts table cannot be determined.

columns.name: etag
columns.description: A unique identifier returned by AWS S3 for each part of a multipart upload, used to verify the integrity and successful upload of that specific part.

columns.name: owner_id
columns.description: Purpose unclear from available data, though likely stores an identifier linking multipart upload parts to the entity or user who initiated the upload process.

columns.name: version
columns.description: Purpose unclear from available data. Likely stores a version identifier or revision number for multipart upload parts, but cannot be determined definitively without sample values.

columns.name: created_at
columns.description: Records the exact moment when each part of a multipart S3 upload was initiated or registered in the system. Automatically captures the timestamp when new upload parts are created to track upload progression and timing.
